cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC 

This paper focuses on developing an end-to-end method for suggesting proactive investigative questions to customer service agents in live-chat dialogue systems. This involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper also considers the human-computer interaction aspect of customer service systems, which falls under the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
